The season of the year precludes the interviews of Daphnis and Chloe. They could no longer meet in the fields, and Daphnis was afraid to excite suspicion by visiting the object of his passion at the cottage of Dryas. He ventures, however, to approach its vicinity, under pretext of laying snares for birds. Engagcd in this employment, he waits a long time without any per son appearing from the house. At length, when about to depart, Dryas himself comes out in pursuit of a dog who had run off with the family dinner.
